What is Feature Engineering (In Your FYP)?
Feature engineering = creating meaningful columns from raw data so the system can make intelligent decisions.

Cosine similarity :
Cosine similarity helps us recommend similar products by comparing feature vectors and finding items with the most similar characteristics, without training a predictive model.

MinMaxScaler:
It normalizes numbers between 0 and 1.
Example:
                      After scaling:
| budget |            | budget |
| ------ |            | ------ |
| 1000   |            | 0.0    |
| 5000   |            | 0.44   |
| 10000  |            | 1.0    |    

Formula used for min max scaling:
                         Xscaled​=​X−Xmin / ​​Xmax​−Xmin
Why we do this?
Because machine learning models work better when all numbers are in similar range.
